ophase: nuclear envelope reforms\"\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\t\"fill-blanks\": {\n\t\tdescription: \"An interactive fill-in-the-blank exercise. The user types answers into input fields. Clicking 'Check' validates answers. Answers are embedded in the content string using triple-underscore syntax.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"interactive_pedagogical\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Text with blanks embedded using the syntax ___answer___ (three underscores before and after the correct answer). The answer text is hidden from the user but used for validation. There can be multiple blanks in one node.\",\n\t\t\tsyntax_rule: \"Use ___ANSWER___ to mark a blank. The word(s) between the triple underscores are the expected correct answers (case-insensitive comparison).\",\n\t\t\texample: \"The speed of light is approximately ___299,792,458___ metres per second. It was first measured by ___Ole Rømer___ in 1676.\",\n\t\t\tmore_examples: [\n\t\t\t\t\"Water is composed of ___two___ hydrogen atoms and ___one___ oxygen atom.\",\n\t\t\t\t\"The derivative of sin(x) is ___cos(x)___.\",\n\t\t\t\t\"Newton's second law states that force equals ___mass___ times ___acceleration___.\"\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n19\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"fill-blanks\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Chemistry exercise\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"The chemical formula for water is ___H₂O___. It is composed of ___two___ hydrogen atoms and ___one___ oxygen atom. Water has a boiling point of ___100___ degrees Celsius at standard pressure.\"\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\t\"flash-card\": {\n\t\tdescription: \"An interactive flashcard deck. Each card has a front (question/term) and a back (answer/definition). Clicking a card flips it with a 3D animation. Navigation arrows cycle through the deck.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"interactive_pedagogical\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"array\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Array of flashcard objects, each with 'front' and 'back' text.\",\n\t\t\titem_schema: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"object\",\n\t\t\t\tfields: {\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Question, term, or prompt shown on the card front.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\tback: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Answer, definition, or explanation shown when the card is flipped.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texample: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"What is a derivative?\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"The instantaneous rate of change of a function at a point.\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"∫ sin(x) dx = ?\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"-cos(x) + C\"\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n20\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"flash-card\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Calculus vocabulary\",\n\t\t\tcontent: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"Derivative\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"Measures the instantaneous rate of change: f'(x) = lim(h→0) [f(x+h)-f(x)]/h\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"Integral\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"Measures the accumulated area under a curve: ∫f(x)dx\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"Limit\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"The value a function approaches as the input approaches a given point.\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tfront: \"Continuity\",\n\t\t\t\t\tback: \"A function is continuous if lim(x→a) f(x) = f(a) for all a in its domain.\"\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\ttoc: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A Table of Contents block listing section titles with their heading levels. Rendered as a structured navigation list.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"navigation_and_reference\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"array\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Array of TOC entry objects, each with a title and heading level.\",\n\t\t\titem_schema: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"object\",\n\t\t\t\tfields: {\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Section title as it appears in the document.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"number\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Heading level (1, 2, or 3). Level 1 has no indent, level 2 is indented 20px, level 3 is indented 40px.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texample: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Introduction\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 1\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Core Concepts\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 2\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"The Derivative\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 3\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n21\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"toc\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Table of Contents\",\n\t\t\tcontent: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"1. Introduction to Calculus\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 1\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"1.1 What is a Limit?\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 2\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"1.2 The Derivative\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 2\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"1.2.1 Chain Rule\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 3\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"1.2.2 Product Rule\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 3\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"2. Integration\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 1\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"2.1 Riemann Sums\",\n\t\t\t\t\tlevel: 2\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tprogress: {\n\t\tdescription: \"An interactive progress checkpoint. Displays a task label with a clickable completion toggle. Users can check it off to mark it done.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"interactive_pedagogical\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The label text describing the learning goal or task to be completed.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"Complete the exercises in Section 3\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tcompleted: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"boolean\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\t\"default\": false,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Initial completion state. Set to true if the task should appear pre-completed.\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n22\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"progress\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Milestone checkpoint\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"Read and understand the chain rule before 