ncepts\",\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tlevel: 2\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tlist: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A bulleted or numbered list, supporting nested sub-items.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"typography_and_layout\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"array\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Array of list items. Each item is either a plain string or an object with 'text' and optional 'children' for nesting.\",\n\t\t\titem_schema: {\n\t\t\t\toneOf: [\n\t\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Simple list item text.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"object\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tfields: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttext: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Item text.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tchildren: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"ListItem[]\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Nested sub-items (same structure, recursive).\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t]\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texample: [\n\t\t\t\t\"First item\",\n\t\t\t\t\"Second item\",\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttext: \"Third with children\",\n\t\t\t\t\tchildren: [\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"Sub-item A\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"Sub-item B\"\n\t\t\t\t\t]\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tordered: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"boolean\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\t\"default\": false,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"If true, renders as a numbered list (1, 2, 3…). If false (default), renders as bullet points.\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n3\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"list\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Key Properties\",\n\t\t\tcontent: [\n\t\t\t\t\"Commutative\",\n\t\t\t\t\"Associative\",\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttext: \"Distributive\",\n\t\t\t\t\tchildren: [\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"Over addition\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\"Over subtraction\"\n\t\t\t\t\t]\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t],\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tordered: false\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tdivider: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A horizontal visual separator between sections. Has no content.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"typography_and_layout\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"null\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Set to null. Dividers carry no content.\",\n\t\t\texample: null\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tstyle: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\t\"default\": \"line\",\n\t\t\t\tvalid_values: [\n\t\t\t\t\t\"line\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"dots\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"stars\"\n\t\t\t\t],\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Visual style of the divider.\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n4\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"divider\",\n\t\t\tcontent: null,\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tstyle: \"dots\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tfootnote: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A small-text annotation or footnote, displayed in reduced font size at the current position in the document.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"typography_and_layout\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The footnote text. Usually short (1–2 sentences).\",\n\t\t\texample: \"¹ Source: Newton, I. (1687). Philosophiæ Naturalis Principia Mathematica.\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n5\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"footnote\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"¹ This approximation holds for small angles (θ < 15°).\"\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tcallout: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A highlighted box with an icon and optional title used to draw attention to warnings, tips, notes, or errors.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"callouts_and_highlights\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The callout body text.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"Always double-check your units before computing a final answer.\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tvariant: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\t\"default\": \"info\",\n\t\t\t\tvalid_values: [\n\t\t\t\t\t\"info\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"warning\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"error\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"success\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\"tip\"\n\t\t\t\t],\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Controls the color scheme and icon. 'info' = blue ℹ, 'warning' = amber ⚠, 'error' = red ✕, 'success' = green ✓, 'tip' = purple 💡.\"\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\ttitle: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Bold title displayed above the body text.\",\n\t\t\t\texample: \"Watch Out!\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n6\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"callout\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Safety note\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"Never mix bleach and ammonia. The reaction produces toxic chloramine gas.\",\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tvariant: \"warning\",\n\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Safety Warning\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tquote: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A styled block quote with optional attribution (author and source).\",\n\t\tcategory: \"callouts_and_highlights\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The quoted text.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"An expert is a man who has made all the mistakes which can be made in a very narrow field.\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tauthor: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Name of the person being quoted.\",\n\t\t\t\texample: \"Niels Bohr\"\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tsource: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Title of the work or context from which the quote is taken.\",\n\t\t\t\texample: \"Interview, 1964\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n7\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"quote\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"Imagination is more important than knowledge.\",\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tauthor: \"Albert Einstein\",\n\t\t\t\tsource: \"The Saturday Evening Post, 1929\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\t\"key-concept\": {\n\t\tdescription: \"A definition block that highlights a technical term and its explanation. Displayed as a bordered card with the term in a distinct style.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"callouts_and_highlights\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The full definition or explanation of the concept.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"A derivative measures the instantaneous rate of change of a function with respect to one of its variables.\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\tterm: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\toptional: false,\n\t\t\t\tdescription: \"The term being defined. Displayed prominently above the definition.\",\n\t\t\t\texample: \"Derivative\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n8\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"key-concept\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Derivative definition\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"The derivative of a function f at a point x is the limit of the difference quotient as h approaches 0.\",\n\t\t\tmeta: {\n\t\t\t\tterm: \"Derivative\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\t\"step-by-step\": {\n\t\tdescription: \"A numbered sequential list of steps, rendered as a visual timeline/stepper. Ideal for algorithms, procedures, or multi-stage explanations.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"callouts_and_highlights\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"array\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Array of step objects, each with a title and description.\",\n\t\t\titem_schema: {\n\t\t\t\ttype: \"object\",\n\t\t\t\tfields: {\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Short step title (shown in bold).\"\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: {\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Detailed explanation of the step.\"\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texample: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Identify the function\",\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Write down f(x) explicitly.\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Apply the power rule\",\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"For f(x) = xⁿ, the derivative is f'(x) = n·xⁿ⁻¹.\"\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n9\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"step-by-step\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Integration procedure\",\n\t\t\tcontent: [\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Identify the integrand\",\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Determine f(x) from the integral ∫f(x)dx.\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Find the antiderivative\",\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Apply integration rules to find F(x) such that F'(x) = f(x).\"\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\ttitle: \"Add the constant\",\n\t\t\t\t\tdescription: \"Append the constant of integration C: F(x) + C.\"\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tmath: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A displayed mathematical formula rendered using KaTeX (LaTeX syntax). Renders as a centred block equation.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"scientific_and_technical\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"A valid LaTeX math expression. Do NOT wrap in $…$ or $$…$$ delimiters — provide the raw LaTeX only.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"E = mc^2\",\n\t\t\tmore_examples: [\n\t\t\t\t\"\\\\int_0^\\\\infty e^{-x^2} dx = \\\\frac{\\\\sqrt{\\\\pi}}{2}\",\n\t\t\t\t\"\\\\sum_{n=1}^{\\\\infty} \\\\frac{1}{n^2} = \\\\frac{\\\\pi^2}{6}\",\n\t\t\t\t\"f'(x) = \\\\lim_{h \\\\to 0} \\\\frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h}\"\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t},\n\t\tmeta: null,\n\t\tfull_example: {\n\t\t\tid: \"n10\",\n\t\t\ttype: \"math\",\n\t\t\tlabel: \"Euler's Identity\",\n\t\t\tcontent: \"e^{i\\\\pi} + 1 = 0\"\n\t\t}\n\t},\n\tcode: {\n\t\tdescription: \"A syntax-highlighted code block with a copy button. Supports all major programming languages via highlight.js.\",\n\t\tcategory: \"scientific_and_technical\",\n\t\tcontent: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"The raw source code as a string. Preserve indentation using \\\\n and spaces/tabs.\",\n\t\t\texample: \"def factorial(n):\\n    if n == 0:\\n        return 1\\n    return n * factorial(n - 1)\"\n\t\t},\n\t\tlanguage: {\n\t\t\ttype: \"string\",\n\t\t\toptional: true,\n\t\t\t\"default\": \"plaintext\",\n\t\t\tdescription: \"Programming language for syntax highlighting. Use lowercase language names.\",\n\t\t\tvalid_values: [\n\t\t\t\t\"python\",\n\t\t\t\t\"javascript\",\n\t\t\t\t\"typescript\",\n\t\t\t\t\"java\",\n\t\t\t\t\"c\",\n\t\t\t\t\"cpp\",\n\t\t\t\t\"csharp\",\n\t\t\t\t\"go\",\n\t\t\t\t\"rust\",\n\t\t\t\t\"swift\",\n\t\t\t\t\"kotlin\",\n\t\t\t\t\"ruby\",\n\t\t\t\t\"php\",\n\t\t\t\t\"bash\",\n\t\t\t\t\"shell\",\n\t\t\t\t\"sql\",\n\t\t\t\t\"html\",\n\t\t\t\t\"css\",\n\t\t\t\t\"json\",\n\t\t\t\t\"yaml\",\n\t\t\t\t\"xml\",\n\t\t\t\t\"markdown\",\n\t\t\t\t\"plaintex